slac.aida

Class NativeChannelProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • slac.aida.NativeChannelProvider
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ChannelProvider

    public class NativeChannelProvider
extends java.lang.Object
    This class defines the entry points to all NativeChannel Providers. All AidaChannelProviders extend this class so that they can access the native Channel Providers to implement their functionality.

      • aidaRequestTable

        protected AidaTable aidaRequestTable(java.lang.String pvUri,
                                     AidaArguments arguments)
        Prototype to be implemented for Tables. This is the most commonly implemented method. Tables are simply a list of arbitrary objects. The object is unpacked based on the channel getterConfig.
        Parameters:
        pvUri - the uri
        arguments - the arguments
        Returns:
        a List of AidaTable to be tabulated either ROW_MAJOR (list of rows) or COLUMN_MAJOR (list of columns)

                                             AidaArguments arguments)
